HEADWORD: Loiterer
<hw>Loi"ter*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
loiters; an idler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An idle vagrant; a tramp.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Sanderson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loiteringly</ent>⟦br⟧
